Package com.github.keenon.lense.gameplay

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Game
    Created by keenon on 9/22/15.
    Game.ArtificialHumanAgreementDisagrementProvider
    This is a simple sampled human provider, that gives ConcatVectors for agreement and disagreement, which do not change from variable to variable or assignment to assignment.
    Game.ArtificialHumanProvider
    This allows the game to configure the kinds of additional io.hybridcrowd.humans it assumes will show up.
    Game.Event
    This represents a single event in the history of a game.
    Game.HumanArrival
    Records that a human has shown up to the system
    Game.HumanExit
    Records that a human has left the system
    Game.HumanJobPosting
    Records that we've made a JobPosting, which will then trigger the acquisition of a human annotator.
    Game.HumanRelease
    Records that we've freed our need for this person before the game completed, which allows them to move on to other tasks, which increases our global utility.
    Game.QueryFailure
    A request to a human fails for some reason, either they crash or quit before answering the question
    Game.QueryLaunch
    Records the launching of a single request.
    Game.QueryResponse
    Receive a response for an initial request.
    Game.TurnIn
    Record that the algorithm elected to turn in the results of the Game.
    Game.Wait
    Record that the algorithm decided to wait.
